Draw a glyph to launch apps or type text — just draw on the overlay and watch it recognise
Switch between TYPE/EXEC/TERM modes by drawing the exec or term glyph as your first stroke
Record custom glyphs in record mode by drawing the same shape in each grid cell
Use dictionary mode to browse all 71 glyphs with animated stroke previews
Strike through a recognised glyph label to remove it from the session
The carousel bar at the bottom shows all available glyphs with live animations
Use bracket mode (draw [, write text, draw ]) for handwriting OCR via Tesseract
